Privacy Policy
Welcome to BibleAnswers.ai ("we," "us," or "our"). We are committed to protecting the privacy of our users ("you" or "your") and maintaining the confidentiality and security of the personal information you provide to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you use our Bible question-answering service.
Information We Collect
User-Provided Information: When you interact with BibleAnswers.ai, we collect the questions you submit and the timestamp of your inquiries.
Device Information: We may collect device-related information, including the type of device you are using, operating system version, and screen size. This helps us optimize and improve our service for different platforms.
IP Address: We may collect your IP address for security, fraud detection, and geolocation purposes.
User Agent: We may collect the user agent string, which contains information about your web browser or client application, to ensure compatibility and enhance the user experience.
Use of Information
Providing Bible Answers: We use the information you provide to process and respond to your Bible-related questions accurately and efficiently.
Service Improvement: We analyze user trends and feedback to improve our service, enhance user experience, and develop new features and functionalities.
Security and Fraud Prevention: We use IP addresses and other collected information for security purposes, such as detecting and preventing fraudulent activity.
Data Sharing and Third Parties
Third-Party Service Providers: We may engage trusted third-party service providers to assist us in delivering our services, and they may have access to your information to perform specific tasks on our behalf. We ensure that these providers handle your information securely and only use it for the intended purposes.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes.
Data Retention
We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. When data is no longer needed, we securely delete or anonymize it.
Data Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.
Updates to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The revised version will be effective as of the updated "Effective Date" stated at the beginning of the policy. We recommend reviewing this Privacy Policy periodically.
Agreement to the Privacy Policy
By using BibleAnswers.ai, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to its terms and conditions.
Liability Limitation
To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, we disclaim all liability, whether based in contract, tort (including negligence), strict liability, or otherwise, arising out of or in connection with your use of BibleAnswers.ai. We shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages, including without limitation, damages for loss of profits, goodwill, data, or other intangible losses, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at hello[at]bibleanswers.ai.
Effective Date: Sept 5, 2023